  <p>
    The Independent School of Jakarta celebrated Batik Day with colour, pride, and a spirit of cultural learning. Pupils, teachers, and staff wore traditional batik attire and took part in activities exploring the cultural importance of batik to Jakarta and Indonesia.
  </p>

  <p>
    The campus was filled with excitement as the ISJ community came together to honour one of Indonesia's most cherished national traditions and deepen their understanding of the country's artistic heritage.
  </p>

